                    Section: 5 - Migrating WordPress for Staging and Development
1 - Site Migration using Plugins
Ensure that local dev environment or Siteground & db opened
Plugin used All-in-One WP Migration - https://wordpress.org/plugins/all-in-one-wp-migration/
Go to  All-in-One WP Migration -> Export -> file - will save site to file and then download it
Create new Wordpress installation
Add All-in-One WP Migration to new WP installation
Go to  All-in-One WP Migration -> Import -> file
You will be warned about overwriting of existing site]
You will have to save permalinks file twice
Plugin automatically searches and replaces custom links


2 - Migrate a Site Manually
Ensure you are logged in to site & database
In localhost you can can make a new folder and copy files from existing installation folder
In siteground you can use the file manager, procedure is
 - Create new folder
 - Go into existing installation 
 - Create zip file of all files in folder
 - Download the file
 - Upload zip file to new folder
 - Extract and delete zip file to free up space
To copy database (localhost)
 - Go to phpmyadmin
 - Add new database
 - Export from existing database
 - Import into new database
 - In wp_options adjust url
To copy database (Siteground)
 - MySql Databases
 - Create database
 - Create User
 - Add user to database
 - phpmyadmin
 - Export from existing database
 - Import into new database
 - In wp_options adjust url
 
wp_config needs to be edited to point to new db

3 - Hosting Differences and Migration Services
Different hosts have different migration experiences
All-in-One WP Migration is used to export to file
File imported into 
 - Siteground
 - Flywheel
Flywheel is quick
Demo of full tier Siteground hosting, staging created automatically

4 - Migrate a Live Site to Local Staging
Cowboy Coding - Working on live site without necessary precautions in place
Create new wordpress installation
All-in-One WP Migration is used to export to file
File imported into localhost
Changes can be made without anybody seeing them
No downtime is needed to take updated site live


5 - Change Theme and Update Live Site



