                    Section: 7 - Premium Plugins and Choosing Plugins
1 - Premium Plugins at WPMUDev.org
Plugins at - https://premium.wpmudev.org/projects/category/plugins/
Multisite - Enable WP on more than one site
The company were originally multisite specialists
They do both themes and plugins
Buddypress - Social Media Plugin
Demo of the course Authors favourite plugins
 - Ultimate Branding - You can custom brand your site dashboard
 - Dev Dashboard - Manages your WPMUDev plugins
 - Defender - Securing and hardening your site
 - Popup-Pro - Configures you popups
 - Snapshot Pro - Backup & Restore
Site works on a monthly\annual subscription

2 - Envato Market for Premium Plugins
Main site - https://envato.com
Theme Site - https://themeforest.net/
Plugin Site - https://codecanyon.net/
Quick demonstration of the Layered Popups plugin

3 - Choosing Plugins from the Repository
Evaluating free wordpress repository plugins
WP repository has huge amount of plugins
Look for the following in any plugin
 - Active Installs
 - Last Updated
 - Version of WP compatible to
 - Version of WP compatible
 - Ratings
 - How many ratings
 - Authors profiles
 - Support Page of plugin in WP

4 - Plugin Speed and Performance Testing
Loading speed is much more important than number of plugins
Extensive notes on increasing WP site speed at 
 - https://github.com/marb61a/Course-Notes/blob/master/Wordpress/WPFaster
Plugins recommended by course author
 - P3 (not updated to the latest version so will be removed)
 - All-in-One WP Migration uses many resources so should be deactivated until needed
 - Code Snippets also should not be activated until needed
 - Simple Lightbox - lightbox for image gallery (High impact on page load speed)
 - Responsive Lightbox - Lightbox plugin for image gallery
 - WP Tiles - tile galleries, very customisable

